protocolDistControlDataSource.name: protocolDistControlDataSource
protocolDistControlDataSource.description: This object identifies the source of the data for which protocol distribution data is collected. This source can be any interface on this device. In order to identify a particular interface, this object shall identify the instance of the ifIndex object, for the desired interface. For example, if an entry were to receive data from interface #1, this object would be set to ifIndex.1. This object may not be modified if the associated protocolDistControlStatus object is equal to valid(1).

protocolDistControlOwner.name: protocolDistControlOwner
protocolDistControlOwner.description: The entity that created this entry in the protocol distribution control table, and is therefore using the resources associated with it.

protocolDistControlStatus.name: protocolDistControlStatus
protocolDistControlStatus.description: The status of this protocol distribution control entry.

protocolDistTable.name: protocolDistTable
protocolDistTable.description: A table of protocol types and associated counts including entries for each different protocol seen by the monitor. Note that protocols are identified by examining the 'ethertype' field of DIX Ethernet frames, the SNAP protocol on IEEE 802 network frames, or the DSAP field of the LLC protocol, also found on IEEE 802 networks.

protocolDistEntry.name: protocolDistEntry
protocolDistEntry.description: A set of counts maintained for each different protocol seen by the agent.

protocolDistIndex.name: protocolDistIndex
protocolDistIndex.description: A value uniquely identifying this protocol distribution control table entry.

protocolDistEthertype.name: protocolDistEthertype
protocolDistEthertype.description: A protocol type identified by the 'ethertype' field found in DIX Ethernet, or in the SNAP protocol on IEEE 802 networks or the DSAP protocol on 802.5 networks.

protocolDistPkts.name: protocolDistPkts
protocolDistPkts.description: A count of the number of packets seen using the protocol identified by the corresponding protocolDistEthertype.

protocolDistOctets.name: protocolDistOctets
protocolDistOctets.description: A count of the number of octets in packets seen using the protocol identified by the corresponding protocolDistEthertype.
